President Obama will be meeting with Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe in Honolulu, Hawaii on December 27, 2016. The purpose of the meeting is to review the progress made in strengthening the U.S.-Japan alliance over the past four years, including cooperation on security, economic, and global challenges. During the visit, the President will join Prime Minister Abe in paying respects at the USS Arizona Memorial at Pearl Harbor to honor those who lost their lives. The meeting aims to highlight the power of reconciliation, as former adversaries have become close allies through common interests and shared values.